"The sea is ours": inland Bolivia hopes the court will reopen the way to the Pacific Ocean
Sailors patrol in front of the naval headquarters in La Paz, which is decorated with ropes.
Above the public buildings, a blue flag flies in the color of the ocean.
The naval bases from Lake Titicaca for the Amazon are described by the motto: “The sea is our right.
